Java 11 focused on cleanup, standardization, performance, and productivity.
🔹 1. Standardized HTTP Client (JEP 321)
    The incubator HTTP client from Java 9/10 became standard.
    HttpClient client = HttpClient.newHttpClient();
    HttpRequest request = HttpRequest.newBuilder()
        .uri(URI.create("https://example.com"))
        .build();

  ✅ Supports HTTP/1.1 & HTTP/2
  ✅ Async and sync calls
  ✅ Replaces HttpURLConnection

🔹 2. New String Methods
    " ".isBlank();          // true
    "Java\n".strip();       // removes whitespace
    "Java".repeat(3);       // JavaJavaJava
    "Hi\nHello".lines();    // Stream of lines

🔹 3. Lambda Enhancements (var in Lambdas)
      Allows var in lambda parameters.
        (var x, var y) -> x + y

🔹 4. Files API Enhancements
      Easy read/write helpers.
      String content = Files.readString(path);
      Files.writeString(path, "Hello Java 11");

🔹 5. Removal of Java EE & CORBA Modules
      Removed from JDK: JAXB, JAX‑WS, CORBA, Activation

🔹 6. Performance & Garbage Collection
      Improved G1 GC
      Better container (Docker) awareness
      Reduced memory footprint
      Important for microservices

